events.name: What’s Next? An introduction to Google Cloud
events.description:
Atmosphere: The Google Cloud Meetup is pleased to announce our inaugural event, “What’s Next?” Join us as well as Googlers Katie McLean and Sean Leighton for an interactive introduction to an entirely new cloud, reimagined for the future.

Together, we will learn about:

The Digital Transformation of the Enterprise

How Google’s scale and tools supercharge Productivity, Analytics, App Development and Operations

Why Machine Learning will change everything

And the best part is, you’ll actually use the world’s most powerful cloud tools throughout the workshop.

So, share this with a friend, and let’s do this! Sign up for Atmosphere: What’s Next, right now!

What to bring:

A laptop

A Gmail account (Don’t have one? No worries! Create a free account here.)

A Google Cloud Platform Demo Account (Get a $300 in Google Cloud Platform credit here.)

Sponsors: This event is sponsored by Imaginea Energy and Google Cloud.

Prerequisites: There are no prerequisites for this event and it is suitable for all skill and experience levels.

If you need help or assistance, please let us know at [masked].

events.name: Google NEXT 2017 LIVE Keynote Viewing Party
events.description:
Join us for the official LIVE Google NEXT keynote viewing party in Calgary!

We will hear from Diane Greene, Sundar Pichai, Eric Schmidt and Fei-Fei Li. We will learn about the latest Google Cloud developments in Big Data, IoT and AI, and get the sneak peek on a tonne of new tools coming in 2017. Look forward to some BIG Machine Learning developments as Fei-Fei Li, one of the world's top ML researchers, and brand new Googler, takes the stage.

It will be an action packed event!

events.name: Cloud OnAir Big Data Series | Session 1: Data Preparation for Analytics
events.description:
https://docs.google.com/drawings/d/18VSzO1eDFBQyCVcId68RZXYLusEJzHc6wh7gzqtXOYI/pub?w=1442&h=454

Data Nerds. UNITE!
Join us for the 4 part Cloud OnAir Big Data webinar series covering the ins and outs of Big Data and Machine Learning.

SESSION 1: Accelerate data preparation for analytics with Google Cloud Dataprep. Sign up now!

Get Started with Google's Brand New Cloud Dataprep. Cloud Dataprep is a new serverless browser-based service that can dramatically cut the time it takes prepare data for analysis, which represents about 80% of the work that data scientists do. It intelligently connects to your data source, identifies data types, identifies anomalies and suggests data transformations. Dataprep automatically creates data pipeline in Google Cloud Dataflow, cleans the data and exports it to BigQuery or other destinations without writing any code. Join us on this webinar to understand how Dataprep can help you to dramatically accelerate your time to insights.

About the OnAir Big Data Series:
Today's applications are generating an unprecedented amount of data from diverse sources within your enterprise. Such data tells a story of your operations environment and your customers in a way that we can now tap efficiently at scale. Sign up for the Cloud OnAir Big Data Series and let Google help you unearth insights in your business and operational environment.

events.name: Cloud OnAir Big Data Series | Session 2: Data Warehousing for the Enterprise
events.description:
Data Nerds. UNITE!
Join us for the 4 part Cloud OnAir Big Data webinar series covering the ins and outs of Big Data and Machine Learning.

SESSION 2: Data Warehousing in the cloud - Google's Vision for the Enterprise. Sign up now!

As industries increasingly take advantage of Big Data and Cloud Computing, it is critical for organizations, even those steeped in deriving value from data, to re-examine the legacy of data warehousing. With the remarkable explosion of data in the digital age, this becomes the form and function of the next evolution in data management for analytics. In this webinar, Chad W. Jennings and Dan McClary, Product Managers from the Google Cloud team will examine how Google's cloud enterprise data warehousing solution is fundamentally changing the paradigm of traditional data warehouse for modern enterprises. Learn how Google BigQuery and surrounding innovations like Cloud Dataflow, Cloud Dataproc, and a variety of machine learning services make Google Cloud the next generation platform for enterprise data warehousing.About the OnAir Big Data Series:

Today's applications are generating an unprecedented amount of data from diverse sources within your enterprise. Such data tells a story of your operations environment and your customers in a way that we can now tap efficiently at scale. Sign up for the Cloud OnAir Big Data Series and let Google help you unearth insights in your business and operational environment.

events.name: Cloud OnAir Big Data Series | Session 3: Streaming Data Real-Time Analytics
events.description:
Data Nerds. UNITE!

Join us for the 4 part Cloud OnAir Big Data webinar series covering the ins and outs of Big Data and Machine Learning.

SESSION 3: An overview of building streaming data real-time analytics solutions on Google Cloud. Sign up now!

Solutions in streaming data real-time analytics enable businesses to take data-driven business decisions and keep a pulse on their businesses. Google Cloud offers fully managed and integrated streaming data analytics services like Cloud Pub/Sub, Cloud Dataflow, Cloud Dataproc and leading open source solutions like Apache Beam to get instant insights from the streaming big datasets. In this webinar, Product Managers Sergei Sokolenko & Kir Titievsky from the Google Cloud team will share with you how you can ingest, process and analyze streaming datasets on Google Cloud Platform.

About the OnAir Big Data Series:

events.name: Learn Google Cloud Basics - Cloud Study Jam
events.description:
Accelerate your cloud competence and career and learn the fundamentals of the cloud with this Study Jam. Go hands on with Google Cloud Platform and learn how set up a production environment to build and run containers on. In addition, learn how Docker and Kubernetes work.

Attend this Study Jam and you will get:
• Access to hands on labs on Docker and Kubernetes
• Official Google Cloud Training through Qwiklabs ($70+ value)

Upon completion of the labs, you will ALSO get Google-hosted badges to add to your LinkedIn and online portfolios show-off your cloud skills to employers.

Please make sure to bring your laptops and chargers since this will be a totally hands-on event.

Study Jams are one in-person session of 3 hours, followed by 2-8 hours of self-study.

We will have Google SWAG (VR Headsets) give away too...

Make sure to bring your laptop.

events.name: Google Cloud Onboard Calgary event (you must register with Google!)
events.description:
Hey Cloud Champions!

We are really excited about Google Cloud Onboard coming to Calgary on May 2nd. This is a great (free!) training opportunity which you might all be interested in!

The event is opened to everyone and this invite is to notify all GDG Cloud Calgary members about this event. This free event is organized by Google. It is important to note that this event is NOT run by GDG Cloud Calgary, but is run by Google. Furthermore, replying to this Meetup will *not* automatically register you!

*IMPORTANT*
YOU MUST REGISTER WITH GOOGLE CLOUD ONBOARD DIRECTLY TO ATTEND
Registration URL below

About the event
Cloud OnBoard is a free instructor-led training event that will provide you a technical introduction to the Google Cloud Platform (GCP). Through a combination of instructor-led presentations and technical demonstrations, you will learn how to get started with as virtual machines, container, applications, big data, and machine learning.

How to register?
Please register directly through the Google Onboard site directly.

* Google Cloud Onboard Calgary - Registration *
https://cloudplatformonline.com/Onboard-Northam.html#register
Note: Fixed number of seats available.

Google will provide further details to you via email.
Website: https://cloudplatformonline.com/Onboard-Northam.html

========================================

April 16th update / further information:

You are invited to attend Google Cloud OnBoard coming to Calgary where you will receive step-by-step technical training from Google's certified instructors.

This fun, full-day event will be delivered by Google's leading technical training instructors using presentations and technical demonstrations. You will be provided with industry best practices and tips to accelerate your learning and ability to build with Google Cloud Platform.

When you register below, you’ll get a free pass for one day of training that has been designed to help you understand and get started with cloud services.

https://cloudplatformonline.com/Onboard-Northam.html?utm_source=googlesales2017-gc-field-eventsgcp-event-google-na_onboard_sales&utm_content=regopen&utm_term=outbound-team

Flutter is Google's mobile UI framework for crafting high-quality native experiences on iOS and Android in record time.

The Flutter Study Jam is based on the Flutter Udacity Course, and we will walk through the first lesson. This will be a hands-on event! Please BYOD (bring your own device)!

events.name: [SOLD OUT - Waitlist] Let's Get Certified. Google Cloud Certification Study Jam
events.description:
[SOLD OUT - Join the Wait list!]

Let's level up your cloud career, together! Get started with one of the Google's 10 industry recognized Cloud and Developer Certifications!

Join the Cloud Certification Study Jam to learn all about the certification tracks, benefits of certification and study and exam tips from Cloud Certified Professionals. Then go hands on with your first Certification courses in Qwiklabs. Together we'll work through several Google Cloud labs focused on entry and intermediate level topics.

ATTENDEES RECEIVE
- Hands-on experience with the Cloud Console, Networking, Security, Kubernetes, Identity and Access Management (IAM)
- Access to the GDGYYC Certification Study forum for help and questions
- Up to two months of ALL ACCESS Qwiklabs

AGENDA
5:00 PM Meet & Greet / Snacks and Drinks
5:15 PM Short Presentations from Google Certified Professionals
5:30 PM Challenge: GCP Architecture (Lab 1)
6:15 PM Break
6:25 PM Cloud Architecture Quest (Lab 2).
7:20 PM Cohort Announcement
7:30 PM Event ends

WHAT TO BRING:
- Laptop (Mac, PC, Chromebook, Linux, everyone is welcome).
- Laptop charger.
- The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best experience, use Firefox or Chrome.
- Library card for WIFI access

DIRECTIONS
We will be in rooms 3-17 A/B. Please provide 10 minutes to get to the room from the ground level of the Library.

Looking forward to seeing you at the event!

events.name: Data, AI and ML Study Jam in EDMONTON!
events.description:
Get hands on training with powerful Data, AI and ML tools in preparation for the biggest Datathon of the year! (see Bonus Event Details below)

Please note: This event is the EDMONTON Study Jam. To sign up for the CALGARY Study Jam go to gdgyyc.link/datastudyjamYYC

WHAT TO EXPECT AT THE EDMONTON STUDY JAM
Together we will work through several official Google Cloud labs including:
Cloud SQL
Cloud ML Engine and Natural Language API
Cloud Dataproc plus much more!

From data beginner to advanced data scientists, there are labs for everyone!

After the live, hands-on Study Jam session, you'll get FREE access to over 100 Data, AI and ML labs that you can finish at home. If you complete all labs in a single quest you can earn Google-hosted badges for your online profile, AND get an additional 30 days access to the training platform to compete any labs you want. Plus, complete any quest to be eligible to win awesome prizes like a Google Home Mini!

But that's not all!

SIGN UP FOR THE BONUS EVENT! THE ATB SOLVE DATATHON!
With your newfound Data and ML skills you will be prepared to join 300 of Alberta’s top data scientists and developers for ATBs "Solve" Datathon, being held in Edmonton, March 29-31. Your team will focus on solving one of three compelling problem areas using Data, AI and ML skills you just gained. It is an awesome opportunity to show off what you’ve learned from the Study Jam AND then immediately apply it to tackling some of Alberta’s biggest challenges. It will be an incredible, not-to-miss weekend!

Sign up for the ATB Datathon at gdgyyc.link/atbdatathon19

Are you ready to kick your Data, AI and ML Skills into high gear? Then let's go!

STUDY JAM ESSENTIALS

AGENDA
6:00 Welcome and Study Jam Overview
6:10 Special Guest Speaker
6:25 First Hands-On Lab Commences
7:00 Dinner Break
7:15 Second Hands-On Lab Commences
8:00 Introduction to the ATB Datathon
8:80 Wrap up, Prizes and Next Steps

WHAT TO BRING
Laptop and Power Cord
Qwiklabs Account (Get a free account at gdgyyc.link/joinqwiklabs)

International Women's Day 2019 is on the horizon and we're here to celebrate Women in Tech! From Ada Lovelace to Grace Hopper to thousands of developers, data scientists and leaders, we're proud of the advancements women have made across the technology industry from Silicon Valley, to here in the heart of the Silicon Prairie. Please join Women Techmakers YYC, and GDG Cloud Calgary for an evening to celebrate, share, support, and inspire women developers, designers, and technology entrepreneurs. We will hear from some of Calgary's rising stars as well as established women from across the industry.

All genders, ages, and skill levels are encouraged to attend and contribute to the event.

events.name: Deep Learning Fellowship
events.description:
Come and join a fellowship of Deep Learning and AI enthusiasts in their quest to keep up with the latest developments in artificial intelligence and cloud computing!

This group is for intermediate and advanced practitioners of deep learning utilizing TensorFlow. Our plan is to organize a weekly or bi-weekly event in which we will collectively analyze the latest and seminal research papers in the field of AI. We will be covering anything from computer vision, natural language processing to deep reinforcement learning and Bayesian networks. These meetups are intended to be an open discussion of the selected paper, related research and relevant model coding.

The first meeting will be focused on Neural Style Transfer based on the paper:

A Neural Algorithm of Artistic Style (https://arxiv.org/pdf/1508.06576.pdf)

Neural Style Transfer is a novel application that highlights a few fascinating properties of neural networks, as well as serving as an introduction to transfer learning and the building of custom models, which will build the foundation for the meetups to come.

Please read the paper beforehand and try to code it up yourself. We will be covering the code in detail at the meetup. As such, we ask that everyone code in TensorFlow and/or Keras so we are all speaking the same language in our discussion.

As this is the first meetup we'll be hosting, it will be a bit more guided than usual. The goal however is to create an interactive study group where we collectively choose the research papers that we'd like to dig into and share the lessons we learn from attempting to execute the architecture in our own applications. Your feedback will be valuable in determining the structure and content of the event in the future.
events.how_to_find_us: We will be meeting in room 2-05C at the Central Library
